Task
Number of even positive array elements
Write a function countEvenPositive that takes arr as an argument and returns the number of even positive elements in the array.
Example:
• the countEvenPositive ([0, -2, -6, 8, 1, 5]) function must return 1;
• the countEvenPositive ([10, -2, 12]) function must return 2;
• the countEvenPositive ([]) function must return 0.

Solution
function countEvenPositive (arr) {
 let even = 0;
 for (let i = 0; i <arr.length; i ++) {
  if (arr [i]> 0 && arr [i]% 2 === 0)
    even ++;
  }
  return even;
}
